<section id="principles" class="section section--ink" aria-labelledby="principles-title">
  <div class="shell">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--reverse">In progress</p>
      <h2 id="principles-title">Built around the talk button.</h2>
      <p>
        These are design principles for work in progress, not claims of released
        hardware support or safety-critical reliability.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-grid">
      <article>
        <p class="principle-grid__index" aria-hidden="true">01</p>
        <h3>Hardware-first</h3>
        <p>
          Talkcan is being designed to work with practical push-to-talk controls.
          It does not require proprietary Talkcan hardware.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <p class="principle-grid__index" aria-hidden="true">02</p>
        <h3>Eyes-free by direction</h3>
        <p>
          The intended live loop minimizes visual attention after configuration.
          The screen supports setup, monitoring, and review.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <p class="principle-grid__index" aria-hidden="true">03</p>
        <h3>User-owned routes</h3>
        <p>
          The channel model is intended to leave destinations and complexity in
          the user's control while the public extension contract remains unsettled.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
